  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>You're traveling the dusty roads of the Tiers, a light breeze cooling the sweat gathered on your brow, when you notice that the usually constant symphony of insects and birds no longer drums against your hearing. Everything has fallen quiet.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>Kills-in-Shadow sniffs the air, her dark fur bristling across her broad shoulders.

"Smell stone whelps on wind. Disguise scent with mud and dung, but Shadowhunter knows stone whelp from wet dirt."

She lowers herself to all fours and lets out a low growl.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>A massive, heavily-furred form lopes onto the road ahead of you, flanked by smaller creatures of similar shape. A glance behind you reveals more of the same. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>The creature before you straightens to her full towering height, beats her chest, and releases a bone-rattling roar that sends a cold shiver through some primal part of your mind. The Beastman beside her takes a step towards you, claws raking the ground, lips curled back over hook-like teeth. A small Beastwoman, her skin a twisted canvas for messy scarification, slaps her palms rhythmically upon the ground. 

Behind you, the other Beasts fan out, cutting off your path of retreat...</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>Attempt to parley.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>Attack the Beasts.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>You draw arms as the pack alpha drops to her front paws, the sinewy musculature of her arms tensing as she prepares to pounce...</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>You step forward without drawing a weapon, hands raised, and call to the Beasts to heed your words... whatever caused this, perhaps you can set it to rights...</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Flee the area.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>You escape unscathed and continue your journey.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>Continue...</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
